Highway 82 through Glenwood Canyon faces weather closures that don't affect I-70 routes to other ski areas. Snow, ice, rock slides, and high winds can shut down canyon access with limited alternative routing options.

**[Car service Denver airport to Vail](https://expresscoloradotransportation.com/car-service-denver-airport-to-vail/)** benefits from I-70 infrastructure that includes multiple weather monitoring stations and regular maintenance. Highway 82 to Snowmass has fewer resources and longer response times for weather-related issues.

During equipment deliveries, I've learned to monitor weather forecasts for the entire route, not just Denver and Snowmass conditions. Conditions in Glenwood Canyon often differ from both ends of the journey and can create unexpected delays.

Transportation companies handle weather delays differently. Some absorb delay costs, others charge extra for weather-related service changes. Clarify these policies when booking because weather delays are common enough to affect travel budgets.

